The `\thanks` command inside the author's list is how to insert a footnote for the authors list. The `\documentclass` declaration should be `\documentclass[twocolumn]{article}` and you should use the `author` tag.
e.g.,

```latex
\documentclass[twocolumn]{article}

\title{My Title}
\author{%
  Author A\thanks{Corresponding author. Email: a@example.com},
  Author B\thanks{Affiliation 1},
  Author C\thanks{Affiliation 2}
}
\date{}

\begin{document}
\maketitle
\end{document}
```

In the `author` tag, use `\thanks{}` followed by the text to appear in the footnote. You can add multiple footnotes for different authors using multiple `\thanks{}` commands. The `\documentclass` command should be set to `article`, but any other standard documentation can be used.

Final Answer: The final answer is $\boxed{\thanks}$
